title: Solve or create note with photo (#655)
message:
Solve or create note with photo (#655)

* Add possibility to attach a photo during note creation or while taking part in a note discussion

* Fix issues for the attachment of photos

* Revert removal of external storage permission, fix tests and save the image paths for a note discussion correctly

* Improvements on the ImageUploader

- removed unnecessary asynchronous code
- abstracted LutimImageUploader to not do anything else than upload images (not delete them, not create the text to put into note)
- Local images are only deleted after the whole process of uploading a note is successful and the note is removed from DB
- note upload uses ImageUploader interface and does neither create nor care what kind of upload service is used
- inject actual LutimImageUploader with base url only at module level

* fix  broken tests

* Center button, remove unnecessary code and other fixes

* Fixed serialization issues, removed unnecessary code and reduced duplicate code

* Better communication between fragments

* add tests for Daos

* rename a layout file

* fix hardcoded size dimensions by using device independent pixels

* add LutimImageUploader test

* rename privacy note addendum string key

* add tests for CreateNoteUpload and OsmNoteQuestChangesUpload

* remove duplicated code that I introduced earlier

* better error-handling for LutimImageUploader: at least log the error

* - replace GridAdapter with RecyclerView

  - performance improvements
  - adapter takes care of creating thumbnails
- have a X button to delete the attached photos
- attached images that are deleted are actually deleted now
- take photo button is a normal button now
- various improvements on AttachPhotoFragment
  - more exception handling
  - rescaling the taken photo
  - keep state on rotation of phone
- fixed nested fragments error
- fixed exif rotation

* nullchecks for programmatically added fragments

* make MapFragment also add its child fragment programmatically instead of layout xml

* slight adaption to exception handling

title: avoid producing quests for access=no ways (#563)
message:
avoid producing quests for access=no ways (#563)

* avoid producing quests for access=no ways

access=no has over 300k usages (roughly 10% of acccess=private)
even stronger access restriction than access=private or synonymous

* allow quests on roads with access=private/no if accessible by foot

* access=no/private without any foot access set also should be filtered out

in that situation explicit foot=no/private may (and should) not appear

title: fix some bugs, correct some namings, add features:
message:
fix some bugs, correct some namings, add features:

- compass mode state was not persistent within one session
- GPS accuracy display was wrong for map rotations other than 0°
- compass view is now a view, not a button, and the compass toggle is now part of the location state button. Rationale: The "third person" view is an extension of the "follow me" functionality plus it works the same in Google maps and Maps.me
- added possibility to tilt and rotate the map manually. Kinda experimental, should not add too much noise.
- the compass is a 3d compass now and shows "N" always right-side up
- added feature that the map tilts in compass mode depending on device tilt. This is experimental, might introduce too much noise through unwanted movement

title: fix fatal typo that can create a faulty commit
message:
fix fatal typo that can create a faulty commit

Details:
If the user answers a quest and the element associated with that quest has been changed in the meantime, StreetComplete attempts an automatic conflict resolution: It downloads the current version of the element from OSM and tries to applies the changeset to the newest element. However, by mistake, StreetComplete retrieved another element (using the ID of the quest and not the ID of the element)
